member.summary:
Converts an unsigned integer to a signed integer.
If the unsigned integer is greater than int.MaxValue it will return
a negative integer starting at -1 for each value greater than int.MaxValue.
I.e., int.MaxValue + 1 returns -1, int.MaxValue + 2 returns -2, int.MaxValue + 3 returns -3, and so forth.

public static int ToInt(this uint value)
{
    if (value > int.MaxValue)
    {
        return System.Convert.ToInt32((value - int.MaxValue) * -1);
    }
    return System.Convert.ToInt32(value);
}

Converts a signed integer to an unsigned integer.
If the signed integer is negative then it will return
a value greater than int.MaxValue starting at +1 for each value below 0.
I.e., -1 returns int.MaxValue + 1, -2 returns int.MaxValue + 2, -3 returns int.MaxValue + 3, and so forth.

public static uint ToUInt(this int value)
{
    return value < 0 
        ? System.Convert.ToUInt32(int.MaxValue + System.Math.Abs(value)) 
        : System.Convert.ToUInt32(value);
}

Returns the default TaskScheduler of the  
TaskFactory's MaximumConcurrencyLevel 
as an unsigned integer.

public static uint MaximumConcurrency(this System.Threading.Tasks.TaskFactory value)
{
    return (value?.Scheduler?.MaximumConcurrencyLevel ?? 0).ToUInt();
}

Evaulates an object for null and returns default if null (for nullable 
types this could be null or a default value). For all other types it returns 
the default of the type (T) provided.
If not null, will attempt a 
direct cast to type (T).

public static T CastAs<T>(this object value)
{
    if (value == null)
    {
        return default;
    }
    return (T)value;
}
